<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="23" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="24.[192,1441,483,1852]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[240,351,1731,1755]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Remark</emphasis>
. The large body [
<quantity box="[564,654,1731,1755]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" unit="mm" value="19.0">19 mm</quantity>
]; mostly or entirely black vestiture of the head and thorax; long ocellar, anterior scutal and scutellar setae; 10-12 thin black marginal bristles; prothoracic and mesothoracic coxae mixed black and white setose, and terminalia longer than segments 5-7 and wide base ventrally with dense tuft of black setae (Fig. 39) distinguish 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bromley" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[878,1009,1827,1851]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Efferia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilosula">
